parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the trunk lid hydraulic supports can cause the trunk lid to suddenly fall, striking individuals and potentially causing injuries, including head trauma, concussions, and ligament damage.
symptoms: the trunk lid does not remain open
the trunk lid closes with guillotine force
the trunk lid hits individuals on the head or body
the hydraulic struts or pistons fail to hold the trunk lid up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive brightness of xenon headlights can cause temporary blindness, distraction, or discomfort to oncoming drivers, pedestrians, or drivers behind, potentially leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Blinding or distracting glare from oncoming vehicles
difficulty seeing while driving due to intense light in rearview or side mirrors
discomfort or annoyance from excessive brightness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic trunk struts can cause the trunk lid to suddenly fall, resulting in physical injury, pain, and swelling to the head, back, and other body parts.
symptoms: the trunk lid does not stay open
the trunk lid closes on its own
the trunk lid is heavy to lift
the trunk lid is difficult to open.
